The paper deals with knowledge representation and reasoning techniques for compliance with the GDPR, which involves data usage policies and consent of data subjects. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The use of OWL2 and its profiles for encoding policies and checking compliance suggests a focus on databases (cs.DB) and semantic web (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of a prototype implementation, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
